  pull(rate)

pivot_longer

Now that the data is tidy, we can use it with other tidyverse functions, such ggplot2:


new_tidy_data |&gt; 
  mutate(year = as.numeric(year)) |&gt;
  ggplot(aes(year, fertility, color = country)) + 
  geom_line()

